{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8f65d808-de5c-475c-9ab2-6f9bc0688022","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0, you need to make these changes in your project file:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line or set to false -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n\n2. That's it — MSTest.Sdk **defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform** when `UseVSTest` is not set (or is `false`).\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n\n- **Running tests:** Use `dotnet test` as before, but you can also run the test executable directly.\n- **CLI options change:** VSTest options like `--logger` become `--report-trx`; `--filter` becomes `--filter` (same name, slightly different syntax).\n- **Extensions:** If you use VSTest adapters/loggers, you'll need their Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents (e.g., `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` for TRX output).\n- **CI pipelines:** Update any `dotnet test` flags that are VSTest-specific.\n\nIf you hit issues, `dotnet test --help` will show the new platform's available options.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2fc4ffe9-6c5d-478f-8648-217dfa277b26","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration, not a code change request in their repository.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":385},"id":"c91bff51-e270-4ae9-965a-9ae86a55c0cc","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:54:15.636Z","parentId":"8c416c47-0a4d-4659-b2ac-6d144e649c01"}
